<dl id="n06040c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06040c">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06040c"> 40(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> went in to sat down &amp; / then got up &amp; went out</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Bient&ocirc;t l&apos;enfant cherche &agrave; se d&eacute;gager de l&apos;influence des mod&egrave;les; mais combien faible encore est l&apos;invention. En voici un exemple curieux: &ldquo;Trois petits ours, sortis pour se promener, trouv&egrave;rent un b&acirc;ton et ils ont tisonn&eacute; le feu avec, et puis alors, avec le b&acirc;ton, ils ont tisonn&eacute; le feu, puis <mark>ils sont sortis pour se promener</mark>.&rdquo; <font color="green">[Soon the child tries to free himself from the influence of the models; but how weak still is the invention. Here is a curious example: &ldquo;Three little bears, going out for a walk, found a stick and they threw it in the fire, and then, with the stick, they threw the fire, then they went out for a walk.&rdquo;]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 20?</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01110c" href="c01all.htm#c01110c">VI.C.01:110(c)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
